IS  - 9
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - S. M. Sinha has formulated a stochastic linear programming problem as a deterministic non linear program, and has shown how to solve this program by solving its dual [1]. Our note extends Sinha's result, by dropping the restriction that the primal constraint set be bounded, and simplifies some of his proofs.
AB  - S. M. Sinha has formulated a stochastic linear programming problem as a deterministic non linear program, and has shown how to solve this program by solving its dual [1]. Our note extends Sinha's result, by dropping the restriction that the primal constraint set be bounded, and simplifies some of his proofs.
