TY  - JOUR
T1  - Jointly Optimal Deterministic Inventory and Replacement Policies
AU  - Falkner, Charles H.
Y1  - 1970/05/01
PY  - 1970
DA  - 1970/05/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.16.9.622
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.16.9.622
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 622
EP  - 635
VL  - 16
IS  - 9
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - A deterministic, continuous time, nonstationary inventory and replacement system model is formulated to find the number of orders, the order quantities, the times at which orders should be placed, and the replacement intervals which minimize the cost of operating, maintaining, and replacing a piece of equipment over a finite time horizon. Conditions are given for when the optimal policy is to buy equipments only when the last inventoried item is ready for replacement. A dynamic programming algorithm is presented for solving this problem. The structure of optimal policies is examined for the stationary case. Finally a computational procedure is given for solving the stationary, infinite horizon case.
AB  - A deterministic, continuous time, nonstationary inventory and replacement system model is formulated to find the number of orders, the order quantities, the times at which orders should be placed, and the replacement intervals which minimize the cost of operating, maintaining, and replacing a piece of equipment over a finite time horizon. Conditions are given for when the optimal policy is to buy equipments only when the last inventoried item is ready for replacement. A dynamic programming algorithm is presented for solving this problem. The structure of optimal policies is examined for the stationary case. Finally a computational procedure is given for solving the stationary, infinite horizon case.
